OL,3,CCharities urge equal access at polling
OL,4,Cstations - what must they provide?
OL,6,FThe RNIB, in an open letter to the
OL,7,Fgovernment, said it found only 13% of
OL,8,Fblind voters felt they could vote in
OL,9,Fsecret during the previous General
OL,10,FElection, in 2019.
OL,12,FWhile less than half (44%) of
OL,13,Fpartially sighted voters said the
OL,14,Fexisting system allowed them to cast
OL,15,Ftheir ballots independently.
OL,17,FThe charity is calling on the
OL,18,Fgovernment to make this General
OL,19,FElection the last "where blind people
OL,20,Fhave to share their vote".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
