OL,3,CCharities urge equal access at polling
OL,4,Cstations - what must they provide?
OL,6,FRespondents spoke of having to vote
OL,7,Foutside polling stations because of a
OL,8,Flack of safe wheelchair access, while
OL,9,Fothers said they felt forced to take
OL,10,Fup the option of a postal vote as they
OL,11,Fsaw it as the only true way to cast an
OL,12,Findependent vote.
OL,14,FIn a statement shared with ITV News,
OL,15,FLouise Rubin, head of policy at Scope,
OL,16,Fsaid: "One in four of us are disabled,
OL,17,Fbut we know from our research that
OL,18,Fvoting in the past has been really
OL,19,Fdifficult and even impossible for some
OL,20,Fdisabled people.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/11
