OL,3,CCharities urge equal access at polling
OL,4,Cstations - what must they provide?
OL,6,F"Issues range from a lack of
OL,7,Faccessible parking, unsafe ramps into
OL,8,Fpolling stations, and booths that are
OL,9,Fthe wrong height or size.
OL,11,F"Disabled people's voices must be
OL,12,Fheard at the ballot box. So many
OL,13,Fgovernment policies have a direct
OL,14,Fimpact on disabled people's lives.
OL,16,F"Life costs a lot more for disabled
OL,17,Fpeople, it's much harder to get into
OL,18,Fand stay in work, and the benefits
OL,19,Fsystem is broken.
